commit.message:
dist/ipmi-fan-control.service.in: Start service after network-online.target

This is necessary when remote sessions are used. This is especially the
case with 100Gbps NICs, like the Mellanox ConnectX-4, which takes more
than a minute to establish a link during boot. ipmi-fan-control would
fail to start and exhaust all of systemd's `on-failure` restarts.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Gunnerson <chillermillerlong@hotmail.com>

commit.message:
Add new hdparm source

With version 0.4.0, ipmi-fan-control will no longer silently ignore
missing or bad sensor readings. However, some drives do not report
temperatures via SMART while in standby. This commit adds a new hdparm
source that uses hdparm's -H option to send an OEM command for querying
a Hitachi/HGST/WD drive's temperature, even when spun down.

Issue: #62

Signed-off-by: Andrew Gunnerson <chillermillerlong@hotmail.com>

Add new hdparm source

With version 0.4.0, ipmi-fan-control will no longer silently ignore
missing or bad sensor readings. However, some drives do not report
temperatures via SMART while in standby. This commit adds a new hdparm
source that uses hdparm's -H option to send an OEM command for querying
a Hitachi/HGST/WD drive's temperature, even when spun down.

commit.message:
Treat out-of-bounds temperature readings as errors

Previously, out-of-bounds temperature readings were ignored if multiple
sources were configured and at least one of them reported a valid value.
This could be dangerous since the user is not notified in any way that
something might be wrong.

Signed-off-by: Andrew Gunnerson <chillermillerlong@hotmail.com>
